This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper introduces a hybrid search approach that combines NMT with statistical machine translation (SMT) models, which involves using probability-based models to generate translations. This approach involves using attention-based NMT models, which are a type of artificial intelligence (AI) model, and therefore, the paper could also be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also involves training and optimizing the NMT model, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which could be categorized under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) or "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
